COPD vs NHB

Diogo M. Camacho

Miguel A. Alcantar

2019-11-16

Abstract

The goal of this project is to computationally identify biomkarers that validate the efficacy of an in-vitro organ-on-chip model of influenza infection. In particular, we hope to identify biomarkers that capture the idiosyncracies of COPD a blanket term used to describe a variety of different lung diseases. Obtaining these biomakers will aid in i) evaluating the models ability to recapitulate disease physiology ii) identifying novel clinical biomarkers that distinguish influenza from other respiratory diseases and iii) aid in the development of therapeutics tageting influenza. These biomarkers will be recovered from RNA-sequencing data capturing gene expression dynamics in a healthy and infected (influenza) model. This project is being conducted in collaboration with the Ingber lab and will utilize their acquired RNA-seq data alongside publicly available datasets.

Notes

  • RNA-seq is of lung epithelial cells
  • there are 5 COPD donors and 4 healthy donors
  • for most conditions, we have 4hr time points of control vs.virus and 18hr time points of control, poly IC, and virus. Only exception is one healthy donor which only has three 18hr virus replicates and one healthy donor with only four control conditions at 4 hrs

  t %>%

  as_tibble %>%
  # as_tibble(scale(t())) %>% 
  dplyr::mutate(., condition_group_time = sample_data$condition_group_time,

pcs <- pcs %>%
  as_tibble %>%
  dplyr::select(., PC1, PC2, PC3) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(., time = sample_data$time) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(., condition = sample_data$condition) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(., group = sample_data$group) %>% 
  dplyr::mutate(., group_time = sample_data$group_time) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(., condition_group = sample_data$condition_group) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(., condition_group_time = sample_data$condition_group_time)

# viral specific genes
fold_thr <- 1
pval_thr <- 0.05

# 4hrs is not interesting, unless

                           which(padj < pval_thr & abs(log2FoldChange) > fold_thr)) 
virus_sig_nhb_18hrs <- with(res_nhb_v18, 
                            which(padj < pval_thr & abs(log2FoldChange) > fold_thr))

                            which(padj < pval_thr & abs(log2FoldChange) > fold_thr))

                             which(padj < pval_thr & abs(log2FoldChange) > fold_thr))
